Maxi vMac
=========

Based on Mini vMac by Paul C. Pratt
http://www.gryphel.com/c/minivmac/

Mini vMac is itself derived from vMac by Philip Cummins.

Original authors
-----------------
Paul C. Pratt          — primary developer of Mini vMac
Philip Cummins         — original vMac; VIA, IWM, SCSI, keyboard,
                         mouse, screen, sony, sound, ROM, SCC devices
Bernd Schmidt          — endian access code (from Un*x Amiga Emulator),
                         M68K CPU emulation foundations
Richard F. Bannister   — screen device, early macOS platform port

Device & feature contributions
-------------------------------
Ross Martin            — FPU emulation integration (2007)
Steve Chamberlin       — Happy Mac icon hack (2016)
Jesus A. Alvarez       — Sony floppy device contributions
Weston Pawlowski       — SCC serial device contributions
Michael Fort           — SCC serial device contributions

Incorporated third-party code
-------------------------------
John R. Hauser         — SoftFloat IEC/IEEE floating-point library
Stanislav Shwartsman   — SoftFloat extensions for Bochs
Bradford L. Barrett    — jdate() function from Webalizer

